{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos510.erdos_510 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos510.erdos_510.","id":"vf_1ac572a0b84753f9","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #510: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. If $A\\subset \\mathbb{Z}$ is a finite set of size $N$ then is there some absolute constant $c>0$ and $\\theta$ such that\\[\\sum_{n\\in A}\\cos(n\\theta) < -cN^{1/2}?\\] Current best: Ruzsa \\cite{Ru04} (improving on an earlier result of Bourgain \\cite{Bo86}), proved an upper bound of\\[-\\exp(O(\\sqrt{\\log N})).\\]Polynomial bounds were proved independently by Bedert \\cite{Be25c} and Jin, Milojevi\\'{c}, Tomon, and Zhang \\cite{JMTZ25}. The best bound follows from the method of Bedert \\cite{Be25c}, which proved the existence of some $c>0$ such that, for all $A$ of size $N$,\\[\\sum_{n\\in A}\\cos(n\\theta) < -cN^{1/7}.\\]The example $A=B-B$, where $B$ is a Sidon set, shows that $N^{1/2}$ would be the best possible here. Prize: no. Tags: analysis.","id":"vf_7c586a3dbd94a61f","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"attempted via frontier '?' (transfer_strength=n/a) -> no_progress","claimed_status":"draft","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_5d6790a3660fe22a","kind":"dead_end","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_5d6790a3660fe22a","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["attempt"],"attempt_count":1,"banked_attempt_count":1,"commits":[{"commit":"121807e20b06eb8148f594dfe13e440181252b0f","repository":"erdos_frontier","source_root":"sha256:210e6e1b2ca15973f38386a512f1f8fa66bbae72bb1b9acb1daf2e669ab279c7"}],"dependency_impact":"problem_local","detail_url":"problems/510.json","draft_proposals":[],"edg